Classes/LCLunaConfiguration.html#/c:objc.abstract: Sign of inclusion of interaction in authorization processes.

Classes/LCLunaConfiguration.html#/c:objc.name: ocrEnabled
Classes/LCLunaConfiguration.html#/c:objc.abstract: A flag to include OCR in authorization processes.

Classes/LCLunaConfiguration.html#/c:objc.name: locationEnabled
Classes/LCLunaConfiguration.html#/c:objc.abstract: A flag to include geolocation in authorization processes. NO by default.

Classes/LCLunaConfiguration.html#/c:objc.name: documentVerificationMatch
Classes/LCLunaConfiguration.html#/c:objc.abstract: Verification threshold of a document with a best shot. 0.7 by default.

Classes/LCBestShotConfiguration.html#/c:.name: estimationThreshold
Classes/LCBestShotConfiguration.html#/c:.abstract: Configuration object of the best shot estimation.

Classes/LCBestShotConfiguration.html#/c:.name: borderDistance
Classes/LCBestShotConfiguration.html#/c:.abstract: Distance between face detection and frame edges.

Classes/LCBestShotConfiguration.html#/c:.name: detectorStep
Classes/LCBestShotConfiguration.html#/c:.abstract: The amount of shots between the face detections. The smaller the number is, the more likely that TrackEngine will detect a new face as soon as it appears in the frame. The higher the number is, the higher the overall performance. Used to balance the performance and face detection frequency. Accepted values vary from 0 to 30, 7 by default.

Classes/LCBestShotConfiguration.html#/c:.name: skipFrames
Classes/LCBestShotConfiguration.html#/c:.abstract: If a face wasn’t detected in the supposed area, TrackEngine waits this amount of shots before it will finish a track. Values vary from 0 to 50, 36 by default.

Classes/LCBestShotConfiguration.html#/c:.name: minimalTrackLength
Classes/LCBestShotConfiguration.html#/c:.abstract: Minimal amount of face detections for a track to be considered as a real face. 5 by default.

Classes/LCBestShotConfiguration.html#/c:.name: numberOfBestShots
Classes/LCBestShotConfiguration.html#/c:.abstract: The amount of the best shots which is necessary to conduct Liveness procedure. 3 by default.

Classes/LCBestShotConfiguration.html#/c:.name: bestShotInterval
Classes/LCBestShotConfiguration.html#/c:.abstract: Minimal time interval between the best shots. Value in seconds. 0.5 by default.

Classes/LCBestShotConfiguration.html#/c:.name: similarityThreshold
Classes/LCBestShotConfiguration.html#/c:.abstract: Maximum possible difference between the best collected shots. 0.01 by default.

Classes/LCBestShotConfiguration.html#/c:.name: checkEyes
Classes/LCBestShotConfiguration.html#/c:.abstract: Check eyes condition. If true then best shots with closed eyes will be skipped
